comment.narrative:
Only 15% of the beneficiaries, or about 50,000 people, believe that the communities' grievances are being addressed by the government. This represents a 27% achievement rate of the 2020 target. 
The main grievances of the communities against the State are:
-	Poor access to basic social services (education, water, health);
-	Lack of economic opportunity;
-	The weak assumption of responsibility for security by the State;
-	Youth unemployment.

77% of beneficiaries claim to have personally contributed to the peace that currently prevails in their communities, with a target of 95% in 2020, for an 81% achievement rate.
This contribution to peace was made through:
-	Participation in peace meetings for 36% of people;
-	The dissemination of messages on peace and social cohesion for 16% of people;
-	Participation in PRT activities for 12% of people;
-	Participation in other community peace initiatives for 11%.
